{"type":"message","id":"a4ae6b89","parentId":"139ea77a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T20:47:36.452Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sessions_list is timing out. This could mean the gateway is slow or there's an issue. But since the heartbeat-state.json shows all sessions as stable and I can't get fresh data due to the gateway timeout, I should stay silent as per the instructions. The instructions say \"If nothing has changed since the last report: Stay SILENT.\"\n\nHowever, the gateway timeout is a bit concerning. Let me try once more with a longer timeout approach... Actually the sessions_list tool itself timed out, which could mean the gateway is under load or there's an issue. \n\nGiven that:\n1. The heartbeat state shows all sessions as stable\n2. I can't get fresh data due to gateway timeout\n\n\n3. The instructions are clear: only send when something changed\n\nI should stay silent. The gateway timeout itself isn't a detected change in the sense of session state changes. But actually, this could be concerning—if the gateway is timing out, it might indicate a problem. Let me try once more to get current data before deciding to stay silent.","thinkingSignature":"38f6ccb481d47d862022c8e0223735284381d8b8c3694e7d2e1291b4264edd07"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bzc04uvwbyjh_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"activeMinutes":120,"messageLimit":1}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":187,"output":246,"cacheRead":14463,"cacheWrite":382,"totalTokens":15278,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776199648831,"responseId":"062ddae20e93977ed9e059f974e37e7f"}}
